Of course, they got the new owners not for nothing: each of the migrants, hoping to facilitate the task of passing the tests, paid for the document seven thousand rubles.
This is more than twice the cost of the official testing procedure: it will cost a migrant worker three thousand.
In the fact that the main task in the near future is to protect the system from corruption, so that the “shells” could not just be bought, both the authorities and human rights defenders agree.
In the meantime, the authorities can promise those who failed to successfully pass the test from the first time, time to study the basic language course.
In addition, visitors who do not know Russian will be offered work in areas that do not involve active communication with people.
