Proportion of crimes with legal weapons is extremely small
The Ministry of Internal Affairs of Russia proposes to tighten the law against the owners of civilian weapons.
This is the reaction of the authorities to recent incidents: to press the shots at weddings, when there were no victims, and the massacre staged by the Moscow lawyer Dmitry Vinogradov, as a result of which seven people died.
Police want to ban the wearing of trauma in public places and raise the age from which you can get a gun license - from 18 years to 21 years.
The idea was supported by the head of the Duma Committee on Security and Anti-Corruption Irina Yarovaya and promised that amendments to the law on weapons will be made to the State Duma in the near future.
Not everyone is happy that the Russian authorities are trying to fight the problem by “twisting the nuts”.
An open letter appeared in the network, the authors of which - representatives of various public shooting organizations - demand to abandon the "senseless tightening".
The percentage of hooliganism with registered weapons is minimal, said the lawyer-forensicist Vasily Lesnikov to the Russian service of the BBC.
According to the statistics of the Ministry of Internal Affairs, for six months of 2012, 142 crimes were committed with the use of firearms registered in the internal affairs bodies, while for the same period, 1168 thousand crimes were recorded.
The authors of the open letter are confident that the tightening of the legislation in the field of civil weapons does not put the criminal to go to the “black” market.
Now, according to them, in Moscow you can find any weapon at a low price.
Meanwhile, the Ministry of Internal Affairs claims to control the situation with the proliferation of illegal weapons.
Suppliers: from factories to officers
The “black” market of weapons is replenished through several channels.
The main channels are five, says retired colonel Viktor Baranets, who worked for ten years in the structure of the Ministry of Education and the General Staff.
