The portal www.bankovnipoplatky.com, which annually conducts a survey on the most absurd bank charges, has now decided to announce a competition for "the most absurd decree or project from the EU workshop".
“We were prompted by the latest event in which the EU plans to adopt a 40 percent quota for women in the administration of major European companies,” said Patrick Nager, the organiser of the survey.
Among the absurdities that have already been put forward for nomination is the recent decision of the European Court of Justice to combine the rate of insurance premiums for men and women.
Until now, women have had life insurance benefits because for insurance companies they are objectively less at risk.
“Further incredible ideas from the EU workshop can be put forward for the competition before the end of this year.
